<CSSBorder-left-color>
<summary>
The <strong><c>border-left-color</c></strong> CSS property sets the color of an element&amp;apos;s left <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border">border</see>. It can also be set with the shorthand CSS properties <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-color">border-color</see> or <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-left">border-left</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/border-left-color.html")</para>
<para>-The border-related CSS shorthand properties: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border">border</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-left">border-left</see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-color">border-color</see>.<br/>-The color-related CSS properties for the other borders: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-right-color">border-right-color</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-bottom-color">border-bottom-color</see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-top-color">border-top-color</see>.<br/>-The other border-related CSS properties applying to the same border: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-left-style">border-left-style</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-left-width">border-left-width</see>.<br/>-The default <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/color_value#currentcolor_keyword"><c>currentcolor</c></see> color value.<br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-left-color"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
